# =====================================================================
# !!!  WARNING — DO NOT EDIT THIS FILE WITH A REAL KEY  !!!
# =====================================================================
# This file is `.env.example` — a TEMPLATE that is COMMITTED TO GIT.
# Putting a real `CURSOR_API_KEY` here = leaking it to the repository
# (origin = github.com/joinwell52-AI/codeflow-pwa is PUBLIC).
#
# Correct workflow:
#
#   1. COPY this file to one of:
#        - ~/.codeflow/v2/.env       (per-user; recommended)
#        - ./codeflow-shell/.env     (project-local; .gitignore-protected)
#   2. EDIT the COPY (not this file). Replace `crsr_REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_KEY`
#      with your real Cursor API key.
#   3. NEVER `git add` your .env file — both paths above are gitignored
#      by `codeflow-shell/.gitignore` line 7 + `!.env.example` re-include.
#
# Both .env files are loaded in order; project-local overrides per-user.
# `process.env` itself overrides BOTH (use `$env:CURSOR_API_KEY=...` for
# one-shot PowerShell runs).
#
# Only the keys whitelisted here are read — every other env var the shell
# sees is ignored, so you can keep these files small and audit-friendly.
# Reference: TASK-20260510-002-PM-to-DEV §三 P1 §1 + codeflow-shell/src/config.ts
# Audit:    REPORT-20260510-007-DEV-to-PM §五 S0 (P0 安全事件 — DO NOT EDIT origin)
# =====================================================================

# ──────────────────────────── Cursor SDK ─────────────────────────────
# Required for the real `CursorSdkAdapter` to fire. Without this key,
# the shell falls back to `InMemorySdkAdapter` (synthetic settle, no
# real LLM calls — good for smoke tests but `decision="needs_human"`).
# Get a key from: https://cursor.com/settings (Account → API keys).
# Cursor keys start with `crsr_` (NOT `ck_`).
# This placeholder is intentionally NOT a valid format — replace ONLY in
# your COPIED .env file.
CURSOR_API_KEY=crsr_REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_REAL_KEY_DO_NOT_EDIT_THIS_FILE

# Default model id for `agent.send()` / `Agent.resume({ model })` ONLY.
#
# v0.2.0-beta.3 (BUG-SDK-007 fix): this variable is NO LONGER forwarded
# to `Agent.create()`. Cursor's backend rejects programmatic model spec
# on Agent.create() for ADMIN-class API keys with a misleading
# "Cannot use this model: <name>" error (the rejected name appears IN
# the "Available models" allowlist, signalling an ACL issue rather than
# a model-name issue). See REPORT-20260511-001-DEV-to-PM §一 for the
# full QA-014 evidence chain.
#
# REQUIRED when CURSOR_LIST_SCOPE=local (the default). The Cursor SDK
# rejects local agents at send() without an explicit model with:
#   "Local SDK agents require an explicit model. Pass model: { id: ... }
#    to Agent.create() or to send(), or run this agent in cloud mode."
# (see REPORT-20260510-009-QA-to-PM §五 BUG-SDK-001 / MT-1).
#
# Pick one supported model id. `default` lets Cursor pick the recommended
# model for your account (safest first choice — survives model rollover
# and works without knowing the exact id). Any explicit id from your
# account's allowlist also works.
#
# Common explicit ids (your account's available list gates what's valid;
# the SDK error message lists the live allowlist on a bad id):
#   default              ← recommended, account-tracked
#   claude-sonnet-4
#   claude-opus-4-7
#   gpt-5.5
#   gpt-5.4
#   claude-sonnet-4-6
#   gemini-3.1-pro
#   kimi-k2.5
#
# Discover live allowlist via `Cursor.models.list()` from the SDK, or
# read it off the SDK's "Cannot use this model" rejection error.
#
# Notes:
#  - `auto` is NOT a valid id (rejected by SDK; see BUG-SDK-003 →
#    REPORT-20260510-013-DEV-to-PM §三).
#  - v0.2.0-beta.3: this var influences `agent.send()` (via
#    Agent.resume({ model })) only — see BUG-SDK-007 fix above.
#
# If you set CURSOR_LIST_SCOPE=cloud below instead of `local`, the SDK
# auto-picks a default and this var becomes optional (still recommended
# for reproducibility).
CURSOR_DEFAULT_MODEL=default

# Optional: `local` (default) or `cloud`. Controls whether
# `Agent.list()` enumerates per-cwd local agents or cross-machine
# cloud agents.
# CURSOR_LIST_SCOPE=local

# ────────────────────────── fcop / pythonia bridge ───────────────────
# P4 sprint Day 1 (TASK-20260511-007 §五 P0-1) — v0.3.0-alpha introduces a
# pythonia bridge to fcop@1.1.0's Python library, so the runtime needs a
# Python 3.10+ interpreter with `fcop` installed.
#
# Why this is REQUIRED on Windows: PATH `python` typically resolves to a
# different Python than the one your `pip install fcop` ran against. On a
# stock Windows install the launcher names are split:
#
#   - PATH `python` / `python3` → often Python 3.9 (Microsoft Store stub)
#   - `py -3` (Python launcher) → your real 3.10+/3.12 with fcop
#
# pythonia (`StdioCom.js:16`) reads `PYTHON_BIN` first and only falls back
# to PATH `python3` / `python`. Without PYTHON_BIN, codeflow-shell will
# print a fatal error at startup (exit code 2, hint message included).
#
# How to set:
#   1. Find the interpreter with fcop: `py -3 -c "import sys, fcop; print(sys.executable, fcop.__version__)"`
#   2. Copy that path into PYTHON_BIN below (Windows path with backslashes is fine).
#   3. If fcop isn't installed yet: `py -3 -m pip install fcop`.
#
# Skip the probe (Day 1 development only — codeflow-shell will refuse to
# call any fcop API):
#   CODEFLOW_SKIP_FCOP_PROBE=1
#
# Reference: REPORT-20260511-005-DEV-to-PM §五 S2 (DEV-005 spike surprise);
#            TASK-20260511-007-PM-to-DEV §四 Day 1.4 + §五 P0-1.
# Replace this with the absolute path to YOUR Python 3.10+ interpreter
# that has fcop installed. Examples (your username will differ):
#   Windows: PYTHON_BIN=C:\Users\<you>\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python312\python.exe
#   macOS:   PYTHON_BIN=/Users/<you>/.pyenv/versions/3.12.9/bin/python3
#   Linux:   PYTHON_BIN=/usr/bin/python3.12
#
# (The placeholder below is intentionally not a real path — replace ONLY
# in your COPIED .env file, not this template.)
PYTHON_BIN=__REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_PYTHON_312_PATH__

# ──────────────────────────── Mobile / Relay ─────────────────────────
# These activate the v0.2 P3 `RelayBridge` that connects the shell to
# the Mobile PWA over WebSocket. P3 is NOT shipped in v0.2.0-alpha
# (P1) — leaving these unset is the right thing for now.
# CODEFLOW_RELAY_URL=wss://ai.chedian.cc/codeflow/ws/
# CODEFLOW_ROOM_KEY=codeflow-replace-with-your-id
# CODEFLOW_RELAY_AUTOCONNECT=true

# ──────────────────────────── Data dir ───────────────────────────────
# Where the shell keeps `agents.json`, `inbox/`, `reviews/`, etc.
# Defaults to `~/.codeflow/v2/`. Use this to point at a project-local
# directory for testing without polluting the user-level state.
# CODEFLOW_DATA_DIR=~/.codeflow/v2
